<number id="1C36CA3EFFB2856A20A1179CF3DA3DB8" box="[391,401,1942,1966]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB2856A20BD179CF3E03DB8" box="[411,427,1942,1966]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113" value="2.0">2</number>
times as wide as head in frontal view (
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB2856A2248179FF1FF3DB8" box="[878,948,1941,1966]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1873,1895]" captionTargetBox="[169,1409,200,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[159,1427,193,1852]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov.. Fig. 4: dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. Fig. 5: head, frontal view. Fig. 6: head, lateral view. Fig. 7: head, dorsal view. Fig. 8: anepisternum. Fig. 9: abdomen. Scale bars of Figs 5 – 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237594/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB2856A2282179FF1FF3DB8" box="[932,948,1941,1966]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); basoflagellomere nearly as long as scape (
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB2856A21B917B3F3483DC4" box="[159,259,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1873,1895]" captionTargetBox="[169,1409,200,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[159,1427,193,1852]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov.. Fig. 4: dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. Fig. 5: head, frontal view. Fig. 6: head, lateral view. Fig. 7: head, dorsal view. Fig. 8: anepisternum. Fig. 9: abdomen. Scale bars of Figs 5 – 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237594/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">
Figs 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB2856A21F117B3F3483DC4" box="[215,259,1977,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum with three transverse golden fasciae; wing hyaline, without dark parts (
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB2856A25EE17B3F7513DC4" box="[1224,1306,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,214,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[158,1428,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 14. Figs 10 – 12: Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov. Fig. 10: wing. Fig. 11: frons. Fig. 12: mesoscutum. Figs 13 – 14: Female Metadon nr. persicus. Fig. 13: frons. Fig. 14: mesoscutum. All scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237595/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="113">
Fig. 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB2856A25DD17B0F7513DC4" box="[1275,1306,1978,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="113" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
