<subSubSection id="E2E48B92FFB7856E21E11771F3CC39F9" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="4" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA41D819FFB7856E21E11771F1C439DD" blockId="4.[151,1436,1915,2012]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,1043]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="4" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB7856F21E11771F3A63D82" bold="true" box="[199,493,1915,1940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="116">
Description of 
<typeStatus id="754566BBFFB7856F20591771F3A33D82" box="[383,488,1915,1940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="116">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity id="6D0675FCFFB7856F23BF1771F14F3D85" box="[665,772,1915,1940]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="4" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB7856F22351771F1183D82" bold="true" box="[787,851,1915,1940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="116">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB7856F22401771F1843D82" box="[870,975,1915,1940]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1873,1895]" captionTargetBox="[169,1409,200,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[159,1427,193,1852]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov.. Fig. 4: dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. Fig. 5: head, frontal view. Fig. 6: head, lateral view. Fig. 7: head, dorsal view. Fig. 8: anepisternum. Fig. 9: abdomen. Scale bars of Figs 5 – 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237594/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="116">
Figs 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB7856F22851771F1FA3D82" box="[931,945,1915,1940]" pageId="4" pageNumber="116" value="5.0">5</number>
–7
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB7856F22C61776F1B03D82" box="[992,1019,1916,1940]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,214,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[158,1428,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 14. Figs 10 – 12: Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov. Fig. 10: wing. Fig. 11: frons. Fig. 12: mesoscutum. Figs 13 – 14: Female Metadon nr. persicus. Fig. 13: frons. Fig. 14: mesoscutum. All scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237595/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="116">11</figureCitation>
). Face, gena and occiput yellowish orange, golden pilose; frons brownish with golden pilosity, half of frons anterolaterally blackish brown extending towards lower eye margin as a narrow black strip; vertex brownish orange; frons, vertex and upper third of postocular margin with numerous black dots; face about 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E22031092F1643AA6" box="[805,815,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E221F1092F1023AA6" box="[825,841,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
times as wide as head, straight in lateral view; oral margin not projected; scape and arista brownish orange, pedicel and basoflagellomere black; basoflagellomere 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E244D10B6F7D73AC2" box="[1387,1436,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="0.93">0.93</number>
times as long as scape and about 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E233C10EAF0633AEE" box="[538,552,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
times as long as pedicel. 
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E227310D5F1E53AEE" bold="true" box="[853,942,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB6856E229910D5F6413AEE" box="[959,1034,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1873,1895]" captionTargetBox="[169,1409,200,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[159,1427,193,1852]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov.. Fig. 4: dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. Fig. 5: head, frontal view. Fig. 6: head, lateral view. Fig. 7: head, dorsal view. Fig. 8: anepisternum. Fig. 9: abdomen. Scale bars of Figs 5 – 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237594/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB6856E253F10EAF67D3AEE" box="[1049,1078,224,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,214,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[158,1428,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 14. Figs 10 – 12: Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov. Fig. 10: wing. Fig. 11: frons. Fig. 12: mesoscutum. Figs 13 – 14: Female Metadon nr. persicus. Fig. 13: frons. Fig. 14: mesoscutum. All scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237595/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">12</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum blackish brown, golden pilose, with three thicker median longitudinal vittae of golden pile and three transverse fasciae of thicker golden pile along anterior margin, transverse suture and posterior margin close to scutellum (dorsal view); postpronotum yellow with golden pilosity; lateral margin of mesoscutum brown; postalar callus dark brown; scutellum semicircular, blackish brown; golden pilose; anepisternum with deep sulcus, blackish brown and entirely golden pilose; anepimeron brownish black, entirely pilose; katepisternum brownish black with golden pilosity in dorsal half, ventral half bare; meron (hypopleuron) brownish black, pilose dorsally; katatergum with long microtrichosity; anatergum brownish orange and with short microtrichosity. 
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E253211D6F61E3BE3" bold="true" box="[1044,1109,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB6856E254C11D6F68B3BE2" box="[1130,1216,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1818,1840]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,214,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[158,1428,193,1797]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 14. Figs 10 – 12: Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov. Fig. 10: wing. Fig. 11: frons. Fig. 12: mesoscutum. Figs 13 – 14: Female Metadon nr. persicus. Fig. 13: frons. Fig. 14: mesoscutum. All scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237595/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E258511D6F68B3BE2" box="[1187,1216,476,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, without infuscated parts; covered predominantly with microtrichosity except narrow posterior portion of cell r 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E24171204F772380A" box="[1329,1337,526,540]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
close to vein Rs, basal 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E206D122DF31E3829" box="[331,341,551,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2046122DF3253829" box="[352,366,551,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
of cell br extending narrowly to apical 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2271122CF12E3829" box="[855,869,550,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2248122CF1303829" box="[878,891,550,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="5.0">5</number>
of cell along vein M, most of cell bm (only posteroapical protion of cell microtrichose), basal 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E23F71241F0903875" box="[721,731,587,611]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E23C31241F0BE3875" box="[741,757,587,611]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
of cell cup and median portion of alula; tegula dark brown, blackish pilose; basicosta dark brown; calypter and halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E22DE1264F67C3891" bold="true" box="[1016,1079,622,647]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Legs.</emphasis>
Yellow, predominantly yellow pilose with a few apparent black pilosity on femora; Coxae blackish brown, yellow pilose; trochanters yellow dorsally and brownish black ventrally, yellow pilose with a few blackish pilosity ventrally. 
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E259812BCF77938D9" bold="true" box="[1214,1330,694,719]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="32C5C49CFFB6856E246012BCF7C738D9" box="[1350,1420,694,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1873,1895]" captionTargetBox="[169,1409,200,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[159,1427,193,1852]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 9. Female holotype of Metadon persicus sp. nov.. Fig. 4: dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm. Fig. 5: head, frontal view. Fig. 6: head, lateral view. Fig. 7: head, dorsal view. Fig. 8: anepisternum. Fig. 9: abdomen. Scale bars of Figs 5 – 9 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237594/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E245B12BDF7C738D9" box="[1405,1420,695,719]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Relatively long, about 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E208412D1F38E38E5" box="[418,453,731,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.4">1.4</number>
times as long as wide; tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E221212D1F10938E5" box="[820,834,731,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
mostly black, anterolaterally brown, yellow pilose; tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E21CF12F5F2BC3901" box="[233,247,767,791]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
orange except for anteromedian semicircular black spot, golden pilose anteriorly, posterior half black pilose; tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E201A1329F301392D" box="[316,330,803,827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
orange in about anterior 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E23541329F037392D" box="[626,636,803,827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E23AE1329F0D3392D" box="[648,664,803,827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
, posterior black portion narrowly extends to anteromedian margin; tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E21CE134DF2BD3949" box="[232,246,839,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
and anterior 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E20B4134DF3D53949" box="[402,414,839,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E208E134DF3FD3949" box="[424,438,839,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
of tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2314134CF00B3949" box="[562,576,838,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="5.0">5</number>
black; posterior 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2223134DF1443949" box="[773,783,839,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E223F134DF1623949" box="[793,809,839,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
of tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2282134CF1F93949" box="[932,946,838,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="5.0">5</number>
orange, tergites 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E2553134CF6D53949" box="[1141,1182,838,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
each with an anterior fascia of golden pile which clearly narrows medially on tergites 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E22881360F1933995" box="[942,984,874,899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
and with a distinct gap on tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E24A81361F7D73995" box="[1422,1436,875,899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
anteromedially, posterior 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E209F1385F38839B1" box="[441,451,911,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E20E81385F39739B1" box="[462,476,911,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
of tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E23731385F02839B1" box="[597,611,911,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
and posterior 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E222E1385F15939B1" box="[776,786,911,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E223B1385F16639B1" box="[797,813,911,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
of tergite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E22831384F1F839B1" box="[933,947,910,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="5.0">5</number>
with mixture of golden and black pilosity; sternite 
<number id="1C36CA3EFFB6856E21D613B9F2B539DD" box="[240,254,947,971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" value="1.0">1</number>
black, yellow pilose, other sternites yellow, yellow pilose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA41D819FFB6856E21E113DCF3CC39F9" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1043]" box="[199,391,982,1007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E21E113DCF34039F9" bold="true" box="[199,267,982,1007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Male.</emphasis>
