<subSubSection id="E2E48B92FFB6856E21E113F0F6A53E04" box="[199,1262,1018,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AA41D819FFB6856E21E113F0F6A53E04" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1043]" box="[199,1262,1018,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E21E113F0F3053E05" bold="true" box="[199,334,1018,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="6DFEA39AFFB6856E20F213F1F07A3E04" box="[468,561,1019,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Metadon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="988A040BFFB6856E20F213F1F07A3E04" box="[468,561,1019,1042]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ [Latin, adjective] refers to 
<collectingCountry id="D2E99889FFB6856E224A13F0F1F83E05" box="[876,947,1018,1043]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Persia</collectingCountry>
, the historical name of 
